  "texts": [
    "The possibility of inverse permutation learning with input padding.We now turn to a more surprising result -simply padding the input is also sufficient to demonstrate a construction that solves the inverse permutation learning task.",
    "Let s ∈ R d be the embedding associated with a special scratch token.",
    "Let S = 1s ⊤ ∈ R d×d be the matrix with d rows where each row is s. We will let s = 0 1×d by convention.",
    "We state this theorem below.Theorem 3.",
    "There exist parameter matrices A (1) and A (2) such that, for any permutation matrix P and target matrix Y, a two-layer decoder-only attention-only transformer parameterized by A (1), A (2) given [P; Y P; S] as input outputs Y to a block of the residual stream."
